'''Johann Nikolaus von Dreyse''' ([[November 20]], [[1787]] - [[December 9]], [[1867]]) was a [[Germany|German]] firearms inventor and manufacturer. He is most famous for producing the "[[Needle gun]]" in 1836,{{Fact|date=June 2008}} which was eventually adopted by the [[Prussian army]] for service in 1841 as the '''Dreyse Zündnadelgewehr''', or ''Prussian Model 1849''.{{Dubious|date=November 2008}}


